# Security and subprocesses

- Many endpoints rely on **`nunet`**, **`docker`**, **`sudo -n`**, **`systemctl`**, **`journalctl`**—failures should become clear API errors (e.g. `FileNotFoundError` handling where already used).
- **Never** build shell commands by concatenating unvalidated user strings; validate paths (no traversal), use argument lists with `subprocess`, and keep parsing strict.
- **Secrets**: DMS passphrase and tokens—follow existing injection/logging rules in `dms_utils`; do not log secrets.
- New privileged behavior may require **sudoers** / packaging updates—note in code comments and MR description when relevant.
